Judge Susan Dlott ordered the IRS to hand over a list of 298 tea party groups targeted by the IRS for extra scrutiny when they applied for tax-exempt status . 
  The IRS has admitted targeting conservative groups with red-flag words like 'patriots' or 'tea party' in their names . 
  Right-wing groups are now able to pursue a class-action lawsuit against the IRS . 
  The agency admitted in 2013 that it was slow-walking applications from conservative groups . 
  The inspector general demanded the list of the groups but the IRS refused to hand it over . 
  The judge ordered the agency to give the list to the plaintiffs . 
 